# Cell IPLs under assets/world/cells/ used to be ignored as lazily-generated
# cache. As of PBD-033 they're source-of-truth: any cell the user edits in
# the Map Builder is saved here on evict / exit and committed alongside the
# rest of the world. PBD-053 closed the pollution loophole: the streamer no
# longer writes procedurally-generated cells to disk on first encounter
# (`load_or_generate_cell` regenerates them on demand instead — pure CPU,
# seeded by coords). Only authored cells reach disk now, via
# `save_dirty_cell` and `save_all_dirty_cells`, both stamping
# `# source=authored` in the IPL header.

# Cooked binary assets — built by the meshconv pipeline (see
# cmake/CookedAssets.cmake). Edit source art under assets/{characters,
# vehicles,weapons}/<pack>/ and rebuild; never commit cooked output.
assets/models/**/*.emesh
assets/models/**/*.eskel
assets/models/**/*.eanim
